item.title: Light L16 Re-engineering
item.description: In early 2018, Light.co released a groundbreaking camera. It was claimed to be engineering marvel. It takes 16 different images and using computational photogrammetry combines the 16 different images into one.

item.title: 10Bit
item.description: A 10-bit image refers to the bit depth of an image, which is a measure of the number of bits used to represent the color of a single pixel. In a 10-bit image, each color channel of a pixel is represented with 10 bits of data.

item.title: Bayer JPEG
item.description: All of these investigations are from @gennyble, Please go say hi! The BayerJPEG is a strange format used by the Light L16… sometimes. We don’t yet know when it switches from it’s normal packed 10-bit raw format to this, or why.
